cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is about improving the performance of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) on computer vision tasks by using the Spatial Transformer Network (STN) method. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new technique for combining multiple STNs, which involves changing the connectivity pattern from sequential to dense. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which are all related to the development and improvement of machine learning algorithms. Finally, the paper's focus on spatial transformations and alignment modules suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics and Control), which deals with the control and manipulation of physical systems.
